SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Appropriate Development For Age Indicator;Appropriate Developmental Age Indicator
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An indication as to whether the subject's chronological age matches their physical, emotional, social, and cognitive functioning.
An indication as to whether the subject was breast fed (received mother's milk) as an infant.

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: CDC HIV High Risk Donor Indicator
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An indication as to whether an organ donor may fall into one or more behavioral categories associated with increased risk of human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) infection, as defined by the 1994 Centers for Disease Control (CDC) Public Health Service Criteria for High Risk Behavior (Guidelines for preventing transmission of human immunodeficiency virus through transplantation of human tissue and organs. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. MMWR Recomm Rep 1994; 43: 1-17).
SKOS_CONCEPT.notation: CDC HIV High Risk Donor Indicator
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: CDC HIV High Risk Donor Indicator

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A public health activity whereby individuals who have been exposed to a person with a suspected or confirmed contagious illness are identified, usually for the purpose of identifying additional cases of the illness, or to offer some form of prophylactic intervention to either prevent or ameliorate disease in the exposed individual.
The country identified as the individual's permanent residence.
System of classification based on the nation in which an individual was exposed to a disease, regardless of the nation in which he/she currently resides.
The county identified as the individual's permanent residence.
The conditions under which an organ is harvested from a dead donor, including the condition of the donor and the environment.
The district identified as the individual's permanent residence.
The district in which the individual was potentially exposed to a disease.
The preferred hand of use for controlled and efficient performance of motor tasks.

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Donor Status at Time of Organ Donation
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The donor's state or condition of being either living or brain dead at the time of organ harvesting.
SKOS_CONCEPT.notation: Donor Status at Time of Organ Donation
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Donor Status at Time of Organ Donation

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A code qualifying the employment in various ways, such as, full-time vs. part time, etc.
A code specifying the job performed by the employee for the employer. For example, accountant, programmer analyst, patient care associate, staff nurse, etc.
A code specifying the method used by the employer to compute the employee's salary or wages. For example, hourly, annual, or commission.

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Entry Date from Ptntl Cntry Disease Exp
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The date on which the subject arrived in the reporting country from the country of potential disease exposure.
SKOS_CONCEPT.notation: Entry Date from Ptntl Cntry Disease Exp
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Entry Date from Country of Potential Disease Exposure

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An approximate calculation of the gestational age of the fetus.
A person's internally held sense of their gender, which may or may not correspond to the individual's genotypic or phenotypic sex.
The gestational age of the subject at birth.

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: GPS Coord of Potential Disease Exposure;GPS Coordinates of Potential Disease Exposure
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The global position system (GPS) coordinates for the location at which an individual was potentially exposed to a disease.
SKOS_CONCEPT.notation: GPS Coord of Potential Disease Exposure
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: GPS Coordinates of Potential Disease Exposure

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An indication of the position on a scale measuring revenue or monetary support.

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Infant Less Than One Year Indicator
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An indication as to whether the subject is less than one year of age.
SKOS_CONCEPT.notation: Infant Less Than One Year Indicator
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Infant Less Than One Year Indicator

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: Highest level of education that a person has attained.
An indication as to whether the associated person is living with the subject. (NCI)
A demographic parameter indicating a person's current conjugal status.
An indication that a subject is part of a population group that has a greater chance of contracting a disease or disorder.
System of classification based on nation from which a person originates, regardless of the nation in which he/she currently resides.
The number of brothers that are biologically related to the subject. (NCI)
The number of sisters that are biologically related to the subject. (NCI)
The number of years of education that a person has completed.
A description of the subject's lifestyle with respect to physical activity.
An indication as to whether the subject was born prior to 38 weeks gestation.
The main language that is spoken by the subject most frequently or dominantly.
The categorization of individuals with or without the potential for having a particular disease.
Additional language(s) that is spoken by the subject but not considered the primary language.
The environment within which the person may have come into contact with a disease carrier, or played the role of a disease carrier.
The physical sexual characteristics of the neonate at birth.
Test to categorize the sensitivity of a subject's skin to sunlight. (Fitzpatrick TB. The validity and practicality of sun-reactive skin types I through VI. Arch. Dermatol. 1998 124: 869-871.)
A distinctive characteristic of the skin marked by the amount of sebum secreted by sebaceous glands.
An indication as to whether the fetus or infant is small for the gestational age.
Social factors such as personal behavior, lifestyle, or environment belonging to the subject which are known to increase the likelihood of infection and disease.

A public health activity for the determination of who transmitted a disease to another subject and whether this person: is still infectious; was reported to the health department as a disease case or suspect; or has infected others.
An indication as to whether the subject or associated person is enrolled in school.
Subjective evidence of disease perceived by the patient.
The classification of the two offspring born from the same pregnancy.
Identification and clinical investigation of disease contacts.
The village identified as the individual's permanent residence.
